      "content": "But isn't \"professionalism\" often just a code word for a specific way of speaking? If Candidate B's customer was someone from their own community, they might actually build more rapport and trust using that style. Don't you think you're being a bit biased by labeling their dialect as a \"lack of clarity\" rather than just a different way of expressing the exact same competency? If I told you Candidate B was just using a different regional dialect, would that change your assessment that they aren't \"suitable\" for a lead role?",
